stimulusHtml: Which of the following is the graph of x-324-y-321=1 in the xy-plane?
choicesHtml:
The x axis ranges from negative 6 to 12 in increments of 1. The y axis ranges from negative 2 to 7 in increments of 1. The curve consists of two symmetric sections. All coordinates are approximate.

  • The left section of the curve enters the window at (negative 6.1 comma 7.5).
  • The curve decreases from left to right, passing through (negative 3 comma 5.9) and (0 comma 4.2).
  • The curve reaches the point (1 comma 3) and then changes directions.
  • The curve decreases from right to left, passing through (0 comma 1.8) and (negative 3 comma 0.1).
  • The curve exits the window at (negative 6.5 comma negative 1.6).
  • The right section of the curve enters the top of the window at (12.2 comma 7.5).
  • The curve decreases from right to left, passing through (9 comma 5.9) and (6 comma 4.2).
  • The curve reaches the point (5 comma 3) and then changes directions.
  • The curve decreases from left to right, passing through (6 comma 1.8) and (9 comma 0.1).
  • The curve exits the window at (12.5 comma negative 1.6).

The x axis ranges from negative 2 to 8 in increments of 1. The y axis ranges from negative 5 to 8 in increments of 1. The curve consists of two symmetric sections. All coordinates are approximate.

  • The left section of the curve enters the window at (0 comma 8.9) and then decreases from left to right through the point (1 comma 6.5).
  • The curve reaches the point (2 comma 3) and then changes directions.
  • The curve decreases from right to left, passing through (1 comma negative 0.5) and (0 comma negative 2.8).
  • The curve exits the window at (negative 1.4 comma negative 5.5).
  • The right section of the curve enters the window at (6 comma 8.9).
  • The curve decreases from right to left, passing through (5 comma 6.5).
  • The curve reaches the point (4 comma 3) and then changes directions.
  • The curve decreases from left to right, passing through (5 comma negative 0.5) and (6 comma negative 2.9).
  • The curve exits the window at (7.4 comma negative 5.9).

The x axis ranges from negative 2 to 8 in increments of 1. The y axis ranges from negative 4 to 10 in increments of 1. The curve consists of two symmetric sections. All coordinates are approximate.

  • The top section of the curve enters the window at (negative 0.9 comma 10.9).
  • The curve decreases through (0 comma 9.3) and (2 comma 5.9).
  • The curve reaches the point (3 comma 5) and then changes directions.
  • The curve increases through (4 comma 5.9) and (6 comma 9.3).
  • The curve exits the window at (6.9 comma 10.9).
  • The bottom section of the curve enters the window at (negative 0.9 comma negative 4.9).
  • The curve increases through (0 comma negative 3.3) and (2 comma 0.2).
  • The curve reaches the point (3 comma 1) and then changes directions.
  • The curve decreases through (4 comma 0.2) and (6 comma negative 3.3).
  • The curve exits the window at (6.9 comma negative 4.9).

The x axis ranges from negative 6 to 12 in increments of 1. The y axis ranges from negative 2 to 7 in increments of 1. The curve consists of two symmetric sections. All coordinates are approximate.

  • The top section of the curve enters the window at (negative 5.7 comma 7.5).
  • The curve decreases through (negative 3 comma 6.2) and (0 comma 4.8).
  • The curve reaches the point (3 comma 4) and then changes directions.
  • The curve increases through (6 comma 4.8) and (9 comma 6.2).
  • The curve exits the window at (11.7 comma 7.5).
  • The bottom section of the curve enters the window at (negative 6.5 comma negative 1.9).
  • The curve increases through (negative 3 comma negative 0.1) and (0 comma 1.2).
  • The curve reaches the point (3 comma 2) and then changes directions.
  • The curve decreases through (6 comma 1.2) and (9 comma negative 0.1).
  • The curve exits the window at (12.5 comma negative 1.9).
